
                                            Seven men wearing blue work suits fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of money. 

                                         CAPE TOWN - At least seven armed robbers have struck at the Stark Ayres Nursery in the Rosebank area in Cape Town.  The men wearing blue work suits fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of money.  No one was wounded.  The police's Sinathi Joni said: “Today at about 11:30 in the morning, about seven male suspects in blue work suits fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of cash. Circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated.”